title.narrative: SOCIAL PROTECTION

description.narrative: Governments have strengthened institutional capacity to develop and deliver equitable child-sensitive social protection systems, particularly in target countries., which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Access To Inclusive Social Protection (Covid), Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Children With Disabilities, Cross Sectoral - Children With Disabilities, Reducing Child Poverty, Reducing Child Poverty (Covid), Social Protection. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, children in the Pacific benefit from an improved policy environment and evidence-based planning and financing.

title.narrative: Governments have strengthened institutional capacity to develop and deliver equitable child-sensitive social protection systems,particularly in target countries.

description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF Pacific provided Pacific Island Countries and Territories (PICTs) with a range of support to strengthen institutional capacity to develop and implement shock-responsive, child-sensitive social protection systems. UNICEF is supporting the development of social protection management information systems (SPMIS) in the Cook Islands and Niue. UNICEF supported the formulation of the first-ever national social protection policies in Samoa and Tokelau. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2022
